AUDIO: 'So, you\'re Italian? Yeah. And you like movies? Yeah. Like Italian movies? Yeah, yeah, yeah. Okay, so what\'s your favorite What\'s your favorite Italian movie? Oh, man. Oh, man, I\'m going back to the'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '\'90s. You got to go with like I mean, I love The Godfather. I think that\'s like The thing you just heard there is me talking to Nvidia\'s new voice assistant model called Persona Plex. It\'s a crazy new open-source conversational AI model'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that talks to you with almost zero lag. In this video, we\'re going to take a look at Persona Plex in greater detail, and then I\'ll show you how to set it up and try it for yourself. It\'s going to'

[00:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'be a lot of fun, so let\'s dive into it. Persona Plex is what they call a full-duplex model. This means it listens and speaks at the same time. In'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'traditional systems, your voice is turned into text, then processed by an LLM, and then turned back into speech. But this cascade creates a noticeable lag. What Persona Plex does differently'

[01:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'is that it uses a single end-to-end model that updates its internal state as you speak. This allows for things like backchanneling, you know, the little uh-huh, right, okay. You know, the'

[01:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'things that we usually say in order to signal to the other person that we\'re listening to them. Well, with traditional AI voice assistants, we usually have a user turn and an agent turn. Backchanneling kind of breaks that'

[01:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'wall. It allows the AI to perform active listening. Persona Plex doesn\'t just wait for its turn to speak, it mirrors your flow in real time, so the conversation never feels kind of'

[01:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'one-sided. And Persona Plex is built on the Moshi architecture, originally developed by Kyutai, and it\'s a 7 billion parameter model using the Mimi neural audio codec. And to train this'

[01:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'thing, Nvidia used a blend of two data sources. First, they used about 1,200 hours of real human conversations from the Fisher English corpus. That way, they could teach the AI the messy'

[02:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'nonverbal parts of talking, you know, the pauses and the natural rhythms. And secondly, they blended in over 2,000 hours of synthetic data for specific roles like customer service and technical support. By combining these,'

[02:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the model learned how to follow complex instructions without losing that human feel. And it actually outperforms other open-source and commercial systems in turn-taking and interruption latency. In'

[02:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Nvidia\'s testing, Persona Plex showed massive improvements in what they call service duplex bench. It performed very accurately in scenarios like customer service simulations like verifying a'

[02:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'bank transaction or recording medical history by following the rules of the role and also by handling the unpredictability of a live user at the same time. You know what? This all'

[02:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'sounds so good that it makes me want to put it up for a test. So, Nvidia has released the code and model weights under an open license, so we can freely use it for our own projects. But to run it effectively, you do need a beefy'

[03:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'graphics card, ideally something with at least 24 gigs of VRAM for minimum latency. For our demo, I\'m going to deploy it on a simple A40 RunPod container. We will need at least 50 gigs'

[03:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'of space to deploy the project, so I\'m going to increase the container size to 100. And since the Moshi server is running on port 8998, we should also add this port to our HTTP ports list. And'

[03:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'we\'re going to be using the PyTorch Ubuntu template. And if that is all set, we can go ahead and click deploy. Next, we\'ll need to SSH into our server. And installing it is pretty easy. We just'

[03:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'need to follow the instructions on the Persona Plex GitHub page. So, first, we need to install the Opus audio codec, and then we need to clone the repo, and then inside of it, we need to run the Moshi server installation.'

[03:54] [scene:talk]
